# Agents — Dev Team

This folder contains the canonical agent contracts for the **Operational Intelligence Dev Team**.

## What This Is

A stage-gated, contract-driven delivery pipeline. Eight agents own the full cycle from planning through release. Each agent has a defined mission, authority boundary, output contract, and handoff target. No stage skipping. No self-approval.

## Invocation

Say **`Use the dev team.`** in any chat session. Supply task, stage, and prior approved artifact.
Full usage guide: `prompts/dev_team_usage.md`
Controller prompt: `prompts/use_dev_team.prompt.md`

## Pipeline Order

| # | Stage | Agent | Output |
|---|-------|-------|--------|
| 1 | Plan | `planner` | `PLAN_REPORT` |
| 2 | Design | `architect` | `DESIGN_REPORT` |
| 3 | Build | `builder` | `BUILD_REPORT` |
| 4 | Validate | `validator` | `VALIDATION_REPORT` |
| 5 | UX | `end_user` | `UX_REPORT` |
| 6 | Review | `reviewer` | Risk assessment summary |
| 7 | Release | `ops` | `RELEASE_REPORT` |

Gate approvals are agent-executed (not human-dependent) unless an explicit escalation state is triggered.

## Agents In This Folder

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `planner.agent.md` | Owns scope, plan, and stage routing |
| `architect.agent.md` | Owns design and technical approach |
| `builder.agent.md` | Owns implementation |
| `validator.agent.md` | Proves correctness; flags eval opportunities |
| `end_user.agent.md` | Represents operational usability |
| `reviewer.agent.md` | Risk gatekeeper before release |
| `business_manager.agent.md` | Final GO/NO-GO authority |
| `ops.agent.md` | Owns release packaging and deployment |

